---
import BaseLayout from '../components/BaseLayout.astro';
import TimelineDiagram from '../components/TimelineDiagram.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Readiness Process" description="Step-by-step CCPA/CPRA readiness process, sprint timeline, and deliverables for technology companies.">
  <section class="content">
    <h1>Readiness Process</h1>

    <p>The readiness sprint is a focused engagement that produces everything you need to pursue CCPA/CPRA compliance with confidence: a complete data inventory, privacy notice gap analysis, consumer rights procedures, and a clear remediation roadmap.</p>

    <div class="section">
      <h2>Sprint Timeline</h2>
      <p>The engagement follows four phases, each building on the outputs of the previous one.</p>
      <TimelineDiagram />
    </div>

    <div class="section">
      <h2>Phase Details</h2>

      <div class="phase-detail">
        <h3>1. Intake &amp; Scoping <span class="phase-duration">Week 1</span></h3>
        <p>We start by understanding your privacy program, data landscape, and compliance context.</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Privacy program review</strong> &mdash; assess existing privacy policies, notices, and procedures</li>
          <li><strong>Data inventory kickoff</strong> &mdash; begin mapping personal information collection, use, and sharing</li>
          <li><strong>Vendor/contractor mapping</strong> &mdash; identify all third parties that receive or process personal information</li>
          <li><strong>Consumer rights workflow assessment</strong> &mdash; evaluate current ability to receive and respond to consumer requests</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="phase-detail">
        <h3>2. Assessment <span class="phase-duration">Week 2&ndash;3</span></h3>
        <p>We evaluate your current privacy posture against CCPA/CPRA requirements.</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Data flow mapping</strong> &mdash; document how personal information moves through your systems, vendors, and partners</li>
          <li><strong>Privacy notice gap analysis</strong> &mdash; compare current notices against CPRA disclosure requirements</li>
          <li><strong>Consent mechanism review</strong> &mdash; assess opt-out, GPC signal handling, and SPI consent flows</li>
          <li><strong>SPI handling evaluation</strong> &mdash; review sensitive personal information practices against CPRA standards</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="phase-detail">
        <h3>3. Outputs <span class="phase-duration">Week 3&ndash;4</span></h3>
        <p>We deliver the artifacts that define your path to privacy compliance.</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Privacy rights response procedures</strong> &mdash; documented workflows for handling all consumer request types</li>
          <li><strong>Vendor contract templates</strong> &mdash; CPRA-compliant service provider and contractor agreement language</li>
          <li><strong>Privacy impact assessment framework</strong> &mdash; methodology for evaluating high-risk processing activities</li>
          <li><strong>Remediation roadmap</strong> &mdash; prioritized plan to close gaps with owners and timelines</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="phase-detail">
        <h3>4. Follow-on <span class="phase-duration">Ongoing</span></h3>
        <p>After the readiness sprint, continued support ensures sustained compliance.</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>GPC/opt-out implementation</strong> &mdash; technical implementation of Global Privacy Control and opt-out preference signals</li>
          <li><strong>CPRA audit compliance</strong> &mdash; preparation for cybersecurity audit requirements under CPRA regulations</li>
          <li><strong>Privacy notice updates</strong> &mdash; ongoing maintenance of privacy disclosures as regulations and practices evolve</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
      <h2>Sprint Deliverables</h2>
      <p>Every readiness sprint produces these minimum deliverables:</p>
      <div class="deliverables-grid">
        <div class="deliverable-item">Personal information data map</div>
        <div class="deliverable-item">Privacy notice gap analysis</div>
        <div class="deliverable-item">Consumer rights response procedures</div>
        <div class="deliverable-item">Vendor/contractor contract review</div>
        <div class="deliverable-item">SPI handling assessment</div>
        <div class="deliverable-item">Opt-out mechanism evaluation</div>
        <div class="deliverable-item">Risk assessment framework</div>
        <div class="deliverable-item">Remediation roadmap</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="section cta-section">
      <h2>Start Your Readiness Sprint</h2>
      <p>Most companies complete the readiness sprint in 3&ndash;4 weeks. The result is a clear, actionable plan to achieve CCPA/CPRA compliance.</p>
      <a href="/about" class="cta-button">Get in Touch</a>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .phase-detail {
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
    padding: 1.5rem;
    background: var(--color-bg-alt);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: var(--radius);
  }

  .phase-detail h3 {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.75rem;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }

  .phase-duration {
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    background: var(--color-bg);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: var(--radius-sm);
    padding: 0.125rem 0.5rem;
  }

  .phase-detail ul {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .deliverables-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
    gap: 0.75rem;
    margin-top: 1rem;
  }

  .deliverable-item {
    background: var(--color-bg-alt);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: var(--radius-sm);
    padding: 0.75rem 1rem;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: var(--color-heading);
  }

  .deliverable-item::before {
    content: '\2713';
    color: var(--color-accent);
    margin-right: 0.5rem;
    font-weight: 700;
  }

  .cta-section {
    text-align: center;
    padding: 2rem;
    background: var(--color-bg-alt);
    border-radius: var(--radius);
  }

  .cta-section p {
    max-width: 36rem;
    margin: 0 auto 1.5rem;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .deliverables-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }
</style>
